        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 2 at 8:01AM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 800 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles northeast of Chowchilla, or 19 miles east of Merced, moving
northwest at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Yosemite Lakes, Planada, Catheys Valley, and Le Grand.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
